    "body": "\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nAdd an `AutotuneListener` callback hook to `knobs.autotuning`, mirroring the existing `CompilationListener` pattern. The listener is invoked after each autotune decision (fresh benchmark or disk cache hit) with the following keyword arguments:\r\n\r\n- `fn` — the unwrapped `JITFunction`\r\n- `key` — the autotune cache key tuple\r\n- `best_config` — the selected `Config`\r\n- `configs_timings` — timing results for all evaluated configs\r\n- `duration` — wall-clock time spent benchmarking (seconds), or `None` on cache hit\r\n- `cache_hit` — whether the result came from disk cache\r\n\r\nThe listener does **not** fire on in-memory cache hits (same key called twice) or single-config autotune (no benchmarking occurs).\r\n\r\n### Usage\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom triton import knobs\r\n\r\ndef my_listener(*, fn, key, best_config, configs_timings, duration, cache_hit):\r\n    print(f\"{fn.__name__}: best={best_config}, took {duration}s, cached={cache_hit}\")\r\n\r\nknobs.autotuning.listener = my_listener\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- `test_autotune_listener_fresh` — verifies all fields are populated on a fresh benchmark\r\n- `test_autotune_listener_in_memory_cache_hit` — verifies the listener does not re-fire for the same key\r\n- `test_autotune_listener_disk_cache_hit` — verifies `cache_hit=True` and `duration=None` when loading from disk cache\r\n- `test_autotune_listener_single_config` — verifies the listener does not fire when only one config exists\r\n\r\n```\r\npytest python/test/unit/runtime/test_autotune_listener.py --device cuda -xvs\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!---\r\nThe core Triton is a small number of people, and we receive many PRs (thank\r\nyou!).  To help us review your code more quickly, **if you are a new\r\ncontributor (less than 3 PRs merged) we ask that you complete the following\r\ntasks and include the filled-out checklist in your PR description.**\r\n\r\nComplete the following tasks before sending your PR, and replace `[ ]` with\r\n`[x]` to indicate you have done them.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n# New contributor declaration\r\n- [x] I am not making a trivial change, such as fixing a typo in a comment.\r\n\r\n- [x] I have written a PR description following these\r\n  [rules](https://cbea.ms/git-commit/#why-not-how).\r\n\r\n- [x] I have run `pre-commit run --from-ref origin/main --to-ref HEAD`.\r\n\r\n- Select one of the following.\r\n  - [x] I have added tests.\r\n    - `/test` for `lit` tests\r\n    - `/unittest` for C++ tests\r\n    - `/python/test` for end-to-end tests\r\n  - [ ] This PR does not need a test because `FILL THIS IN`.\r\n\r\n- Select one of the following.\r\n  - [x] I have not added any `lit` tests.\r\n  - [x] The `lit` tests I have added follow these [best practices](https://mlir.llvm.org/getting_started/TestingGuide/#filecheck-best-practices),\r\n    including the \"tests should be minimal\" section. (Usually running Python code\r\n    and using the instructions it generates is not minimal.)\r\n",
